gmd:abstract.gco:CharacterString: These polygon and point data layers represent PLSS for Washburn County, Wisconsin in 2017. They are feature classes within the geodatabase, Washburn_PLSS_2017.gdb. The features included in this geodatabase are 'WASHBURN_PLSS_2017', 'WASHBURN_SECTION_CORNERS' and 'WASHBURN_SECTIONPOLY_2017'.

gmd:purpose.gco:CharacterString: This layer is intended for reference and mapping purposes, and may be used for basic applications such as viewing, querying, and map output production, or to provide a basemap to support graphical overlays and analysis with other spatial data.

gmd:supplementalInformation.gco:CharacterString: This data was submitted to the UW geospatial archive in 2017. Content may be considered current as of December 31, 2016. It was published to the UW geospatial archive as part of the Wisconsin Department of Administration Land Information Program annual collection of public data for the year 2017.

gmd:measureDescription.gco:CharacterString: Attribute information remains the same as given by the author of the data.

gmd:description.gco:CharacterString: Created new feature dataset 'Washburn_PLSS_2017' within the geodatabase 'Washburn_PLSS_2017' .
Exported original feature class into a new file geodatabase to maintain the original file format of the data and to conform to UW-Madison's data distribution plan.
The data for this layer was published with multiple feature classes, and the metadata was generated at the feature data class level 'WASHBURN_PLSS_2017' .

gmd:maintenanceNote.gco:CharacterString: Metadata was translated to ISO 19139 for inclusion in the Big Ten Academic Alliance Geoportal.
